        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 5:02PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Spade, or 5 miles east of Littlefield, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Littlefield, Cotton Center, and Spade.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
